ciscoIetfDot11QosExtMIB.name: ciscoIetfDot11QosExtMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoIetfDot11QosExtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive, San Jose CA 95134-1706. USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-dot11@cisco.com
ciscoIetfDot11QosExtMIB.description: This MIB module provides network management support for QoS on IEEE 802.11 wireless LAN devices. This MIB is an extension to QoS MIB defined in IEEE 802.11E standard.

cid11QosExtConfigTable.name: cid11QosExtConfigTable
cid11QosExtConfigTable.description: This table contains the basic set of attributes to configure QoS for a wireless LAN device. This table has a sparse dependent relationship with the ifTable. Each IEEE 802.11 wireless interface has a set of configuration parameters for each IP network traffic category. For each entry in this table, there exists an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71).

cid11QosExtConfigEntry.name: cid11QosExtConfigEntry
cid11QosExtConfigEntry.description: Each entry contains parameters to configure traffic control on an IEEE 802.11 radio interface.

cid11QosExtBackoffOffset.name: cid11QosExtBackoffOffset
cid11QosExtBackoffOffset.description: This specifies the offset of the radio backoff from the transmission media for this traffic category. The backoff interval of a radio is calculated from a pseudo random integer drawn from a uniform distribution over the interval determined by the maximum and minimum of the contention window.

cid11QosExtMaxRetry.name: cid11QosExtMaxRetry
cid11QosExtMaxRetry.description: This specifies the number of times the radio retries for a particular transmission if there is a collision for the media.

cid11QosExtIfConfigTable.name: cid11QosExtIfConfigTable
cid11QosExtIfConfigTable.description: This table contains the attributes indicating QoS support information on the IEEE 802.11 radio interfaces. This table has a sparse dependent relationship with the ifTable. For each entry in this table, there exists an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71).

cid11QosExtIfConfigEntry.name: cid11QosExtIfConfigEntry
cid11QosExtIfConfigEntry.description: Each entry contains attributes to configure QoS for an IEEE 802.11 interface.

cid11QosExtOptionEnabled.name: cid11QosExtOptionEnabled
cid11QosExtOptionEnabled.description: This object indicates if QoS is enabled on this IEEE 802.11 network interface. If it is 'true', QoS queueing is on and traffic is prioritized according to traffic categories. It it is 'false', there is no QoS queueing and traffic is not prioritized.

cid11QosExtVlanTable.name: cid11QosExtVlanTable
cid11QosExtVlanTable.description: This table contains attributes for traffic classification of VLANs. This table has a one-to-one dependent relationship to the cwvlWlanVlanTable in the CISCO-WLAN-VLAN-MIB.

cid11QosExtVlanEntry.name: cid11QosExtVlanEntry
cid11QosExtVlanEntry.description: Each entry includes parameters determining the class of service (category) of the traffic and QoS configuration on the VLAN.

cid11QosExtVlanClassOfService.name: cid11QosExtVlanClassOfService
cid11QosExtVlanClassOfService.description: This is the class of service classification to the traffic transmitting on this VLAN. The class of service determines the priority of the traffic. The default VLAN for voice traffic is '4095', and the default service classification is 'interactiveVoice'. The classification on the VLAN '4095' cannot be modified by the network management system. The service classification on all other VLANs are 'bestEffort'.

cid11QosExtQueueTable.name: cid11QosExtQueueTable
cid11QosExtQueueTable.description: This table contains the priority queue configuration attributes for IEEE 802.11 radio interface. This table has a sparse dependent relationship with the ifTable. For each entry in this table, there exists an entry in the ifTable of ifType ieee80211(71).

cid11QosExtQueueEntry.name: cid11QosExtQueueEntry
cid11QosExtQueueEntry.description: A collection of attributes to configure the priority queues for each traffic category on an IEEE 802.11 interface.

cid11QosExtQueueQuota.name: cid11QosExtQueueQuota
cid11QosExtQueueQuota.description: This is the current QoS priority queue packet quota for the traffic category on the overall bandwidth. The total quota is 12 and is shared among 8 transmitting queues. The queue with the largest quota value has the largest share of the overall bandwidth of the radio. The quota is allocated by the radio driver dynamically.

cid11QosExtNotifEnabled.name: cid11QosExtNotifEnabled
cid11QosExtNotifEnabled.description: Indicates whether ciscoIetfDot11QosExtChangeNotif notifications will or will not be sent by the agent when the QoS configuration in the cid11QosExtIfConfigTable and cid11QosConfigTable defined in the CISCO-IETF-DOT11-QOS-MIB are changed.

ciscoIetfDot11QosExtChangeNotif.name: ciscoIetfDot11QosExtChangeNotif
ciscoIetfDot11QosExtChangeNotif.description: This ciscoIetfDot11QosExtChangeNotif notification will be sent when the QoS configuration in the cid11QosExtIfConfigTable or the cid11QosConfigTable defined in the CISCO-IETF-DOT11-QOS-MIB are changed. The object cid11TrafficPriority defined in the cid11QosConfigTable specifies the traffic priority of the configuration that changed. The sending of these notifications can be enabled or disabled via the cid11QosExtNotifEnabled object.

ciscoIetfD11QosExtMIBCompliance.name: ciscoIetfD11QosExtMIBCompliance
ciscoIetfD11QosExtMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the configuration and status groups.

ciscoIetfD11QosExtNotifGroup.name: ciscoIetfD11QosExtNotifGroup
ciscoIetfD11QosExtNotifGroup.description: This is the notification group for the CISCO-IETF-DOT11-QOS-EXT-MIB.
